HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 350
BY REPRESENTATIVE FREEMAN
A RESOLUTION
To designate Sunday, June 7, 2026, as Reggio Family Clock Donation Day in Louisiana.
WHEREAS, Louisiana citizens are heirs to and benefactors of a rich and diverse
historical tapestry; and
WHEREAS, each year, communities and museums across Louisiana celebrate the
history of the state and its artifacts; and
WHEREAS, in museums across Louisiana, precious artifacts are curated and
preserved and presented to the citizens of Louisiana and those interested in gaining a broader
understanding of the past, present, and hope for the future of the state; and
WHEREAS, Godfrey "Frey" Reggio, III, and the Reggio family will present the
Reggio Family Clock to the Cabildo in New Orleans for display as a part of its permanent
collections during the Gálvez and Louisiana in the American Revolution exhibition; and
WHEREAS, this timepiece was crafted around 1751 and has been handed down from
its original owner, François Marie, Chevalier de Reggio; the artifact is a small but tangible
link to the objects and people present during some of most pivotal moments in Louisiana
history.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Sunday, June 7, 2026, as Reggio Family
Clock Donation Day in Louisiana and does hereby encourage all citizens of Louisiana to
share in the joy of this special day.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
